37528>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
37528>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
37528>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
37531>>>
37531>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37531>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37531>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37531>>>        Case Begin
37531>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37533>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37533>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37533>>>                Case Break
37534>>>                
37534>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37537>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37537>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37537>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37537>>>                Case Break
37538>>>                
37538>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37541>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37541>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37541>>>                Case Break
37542>>>                
37542>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37542>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37542>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37542>>>                  
37542>>>        Case End
37542>>>
37542>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37542>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37542>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37543>>>
37543>>>    End_Procedure
37544>>>
37544>>>End_Object
